Remarks. This species is similar to
Areekulus eugeniae
Chandrapatya, 1998
(
Boczek & Chandrapatya, 1998
)
, but can be differentiated by female genital coverflap with irregular short lines (female genital coverflap smooth in
A . eugeniae
), dorsal annuli smooth (dorsal annuli with microtubercles in
A . eugeniae
), paraxial tibial setae ( l' ) absent (paraxial tibial setae ( l' ) present in
A . eugeniae
).
